var e=[{front:`What is the difference between DFS and BFS?`,back:`DFS explores as far as possible before backtracking, BFS explores all neighbors at current distance first.`},{front:`Which search algorithm guarantees shortest path?`,back:`BFS (breadth-first search) guarantees shortest path when all edge costs are equal.`},{front:`What is A* search?`,back:`Combines actual cost from start with heuristic estimate to goal: f(n) = g(n) + h(n).`},{front:`What makes a heuristic admissible?`,back:`It never overestimates the actual cost to reach the goal.`},{front:`What is minimax algorithm?`,back:`Algorithm for adversarial search where maximizer and minimizer alternate choosing best moves.`},{front:`What does alpha-beta pruning do?`,back:`Eliminates branches in minimax that can't affect the final result, improving efficiency.`}];export{e as default};